Biancamaria Florenzi

r0777934

Progesterone Receptor Transcriptome and Cistrome in Decidualized Human Endometrial Stroma Cells¶

The reference literature is available at:

Mazur EC, Vasquez YM, Li X, Kommagani R, Jiang L, Chen R, Lanz RB, Kovanci E, Gibbons WE, DeMayo FJ. Progesterone receptor transcriptome and cistrome in decidualized human endometrial stromal cells. Endocrinology. 2015 Jun;156(6):2239-53. doi: 10.1210/en.2014-1566. Epub 2015 Mar 17. PMID: 25781565; PMCID: PMC4430623.

The Chip-seq data has been downloaded from SRA, where it is available at the following link:

https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sra?term=SRP059136

In the experiment, Chromatin-Immunoprecipitation sequencing data have been generated, using Illumina platform, with antibody against PGR (progesterone receptor), FOSL2 (composes AP-1 transcription factor) and no antibody (for control) on human endometrial stroma cells in which in vitro decidualization had been triggered. The study is part of a superstudy, in which differential expression levels have also been investigated with RNA-seq, with the purpose of gaining better insight into the process of decidualization. Decidualization is a complex process fundamental for enstablishing and supporting a pregnancy, of which the ovarian steroid hormone progesterone, that acts through its necluear receptor, is a key player. Nuclear hormone receptors classically bind directly to DNA in promoter regions, regulating the expression or silencing of particular genes (direct targets), or they have protein-protein interactions with other TF that bind to the DNA (indirect regulation).

Note: Endometrium = inner lining of the uterus, where the embryo implants upon conception

I decided to conduct the analysis in parallel with PGR and FOSL2, as I thought this would give me the opportunity to compare the findings and quality of the analysis. I also hope to obtain overlaps between the target genes.

Peak calling with MACS2¶

MACS2 is one of the most commonly used peak callers; i run the callpeak function of the target bam (PGR or FOSL2) and the control input. The genome size is the same used before, while the q-value is the cutoff used.

Motif analysis¶

De novo motif discovery with RSAT¶

Used fetch-sequences from Sequence tools in RSAT to get the fasta files of the peaks from the bed file of the peaks and then ran peak-motifs from NGS-Chip-seq. I did this for both FOSL2 and PGR.

PGR result:

FOSL2 report

i-cisTarget for PGR¶

We test for enrichment of motifs against a database. From Chip-seq narrowpeak file. I ran i-cis target from the narrowPeak file that I have obtained from MACS2. The result shows a list of motifs and possible target genes, and the PGR human is found in position 13, while different versions of it, or similar, are present in the first position of the ranking. Indeed, PGR is also known as NR3C3, and we find NR3C1 and NR3C2.

I download the candidate site for the targets of the PGR TF, according to i-cis Target, because I want to connect those sites to genes.

Conclusion¶
I expected to find more overlap between the genes that are selected integrating the information from i-cis Target and STRING, between the two analysis. Nevertheless, the target genes found by GREAT linked to the candidate sites are all related to an appropriate set of terms and process, both for PGR and FOSL2; their involvement in the decidualization process has probably not been accurately described during my assignment, but surely shown.
